we have been trying to use SYSID in order to get kp,ki,kd,ks,kv, and ka constants of our drivetrain with SYSID but the robot doesn’t move in any way.
it happened last year as well but we have managed to find a workaround using SysidJavaLogger for this year Sysid says that the data doesn’t get to the NT Entry I checked it in the Sysid code and the entry hasn’t changed.
if anyone has a solution it would be very appreciated things I have tried include:
downloading a new wpilib suite
compiling Sysid
the robot it selfs works with the regular code and so with the Sysid Code (there are no errors reported). when enabling the autonomous robot, SparkMax does not show any voltage going to the motors. here are the IDs of the motors:
10 left forward
11 left Backward
12 right forward
13 right backward

WhatsApp Image 2023-02-02 at 17.53.581080×1920 233 KB

I have played with the motor’s ID in which slot are they but it hasn’t worked.
